@NODE About "About MagicSelector"
@TOC Main
 About MagicSelector               @{b}Important Information@{ub}

 This software is provided as-is, without warranty either expressed or implied.
 In no event will the author be liable for direct,indirect, incidental or consequential
 damages or loss of data resulting from the use of this software.  The risk as to results
 and performance of this software is assumed entirely by the user.

 MagicSelector is shareware, so if you find it useful, and use it regularly, I ask that
 you register MagicSelector for $10.00 (U.S.). If you really cannot afford the $10.00 fee,
 you may send me a registered version of a program you wrote that you feel is comparable to
 MagicSelector.

 This program cannot be used for commercial purposes without written permission from the author.
 Special permission is hereby granted to include MagicSelector in Public-Domain collections
 such as Fred Fish's Amiga Library, Aminet CD ROMS, etc.

 @{b}What Is MagicSelector@{ub}

 MagicSelector is a program who select different background and sound in Workbench each time you
 are booting up you Amiga.

 I have written two programs that helps, me to select an background and a sound for each startup.

 These two programs are:

	@{"  MagicSelector Preferences  " LINK MagicSelectorPreferences}
	@{"  MagicSelector  " LINK MagicSelector}

 I had to build an MagicSelector Preferences, so the user can specify the files he want to use in
 Workbench.

 MagicSelector is the main program, that set up you background(s) and Sound.

 MagicSelector software and documentation are © 1994 by Řyvind Falch, Triumph Software.
 All rights reserved.

 For Registration see @{"Registration" LINK Registration}.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Requirements "Requirements"
@TOC Main
 MagicSelector should run on any Amiga system with at least 512K RAM.

 @{b}MagicSelector requires:@{ub}

 KickStart v3.0 or greater 
 asl.library
 datatype.library
 8SVX datatype
 MUImaster.library V2.2+
 MUI-Classes
 Sys:Prefs/WBPattern
 sys:Prefs/Sound

 I have not included MUI since this would have made the archive a lot bigger. If the MUI-package
 is not yet in your possession, you should be able to find it at several Public Domain sites
 around the world, your local BBS or on Public Domain Disks.

 The Graphical User Interface (GUI) was created using the great MUImaster.library V2.2 @{" MUI " LINK MUI},
 Copyrighted 1992/94 Stefan Stuntz.


@ENDNODE

